The paper deals with rate-distortion functions, which are typically studied in information theory (cs.IT). The use of dithered lattice quantization and entropy coding suggests a focus on multimedia applications (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the causal nature of the achieved rate-distortion function, which could fall under the category of causal inference (cs.SI). Finally, the use of infinite dimensional quantizers and the analysis of rate loss in the finite dimensional case suggests a focus on mathematical aspects of the problem, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
